President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Carolyn Watts Colvin as Commissioner of Social Security. Colvin is currently the Deputy Commissioner of Social Security for the Social Security Administration (SSA) and has been in that position since January 2011. She has also been serving as Acting Commissioner of Social Security since February 2013. Colvin has had a long career in various roles, including being the Chief Executive Officer of Amerigroup Community Care of D.C., the Director of the Montgomery County Department of Health and Human Services, and the Director of the District of Columbia Department of Health and Human Services. She has also served in various roles at the Social Security Administration from 1994 to 2001. Colvin received her B.A. and M.B.A. from Morgan State University. President Obama expressed gratitude for Colvin's past service and confidence in her ability to serve the American people well in her new role.